24/10/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Police announced on Saturday (22 October) the arrest of a Croatian national suspected of committing war crimes against civilians from 1991-1995. 
The 60-year old man, whose name and ethnic background was not revealed, was arrested Friday in Pula. 
He is accused of committing war crimes against the civilian population of Karlovac as a member of "enemy military units". 
(HRT - 22/10/05)
